main event: A light crossed in front of the moon from left to right on November 12, 1957.
interesting points: The observation was made at 10:30 p.m. from Corona del Mar, California., The object appeared to be a maroon-black cone or fin shape., The light was moving in a straight line across the face of the moon., The observer noted they were completely sober at the time., Insufficient data was provided for analysis in the report.
sighted object: a light moving across the moon
witness description: The witness had just attended a city council meeting and was driving home when the sighting occurred.
